Shirley Booth (August 30, 1898 – October 16, 1992) was an American actress who appeared on stage, in films, on radio, and on television.
Booth’s Broadway career started in 1925 as a theatrical actor, but she also appeared in films and television. One of her most notable roles was as Lola Delaney in the Broadway play Come Back, Little Sheba, for which she won a Tony Award in 1950.

